Updated `/home/dave/Projects/jaynes-archive/content/papers/electrodynamics.today.md` with minimal structural QA edits only.

Summary of changes:
- Converted citation superscripts like `$^{n}$` to Hugo/Markdown footnotes `[^n]`.
- Converted the `## REFERENCES` numbered list into proper footnote definitions `[^n]: ...` (content preserved).
- Added missing blank-line paragraph breaks where prose paragraphs were incorrectly joined.
- Fixed display-equation readability where prose was on the same line as equation blocks.
- Added equation tags so all in-text equation references resolve to visible numbers:
  - `\tag{3}` on `(W_{ZP})_{eff}` equation
  - `\tag{9}` on the Volterra equation
  - `\tag{12}` on the damped-oscillation `G(t)` equation
  - `\tag{19}` on the final subtraction-physics line-shift equation
- Added a blank line before the numbered list in the addendum so Markdown list rendering is clean.

Self-check completed:
- Paragraph boundaries now use blank lines where intended.
- In-text equation references `(3)`, `(9)`, `(12)`, and `Eq. (19)` are now discoverable on tagged display equations.
